echnology can significantly aid forest management by leveraging tools such as remote sensing, GIS, IoT sensor networks, and AI. These technologies can be employed for tasks such as monitoring forest health, detecting wildfires, tracking biodiversity, and predicting environmental changes. Additionally, blockchain can ensure the transparency and legality of timber supply chains, while mobile apps facilitate reporting and community engagement. Automated inventory management, data analytics, and educational VR/AR experiences further enhance the efficiency and effectiveness of forest management practices. Overall, technology offers innovative solutions for sustainable and data-driven forest conservation.
